                        <div class="1593530441879 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="22383a33-5e36-4c95-88ec-52d304ba251c" >

    <p>The course introduces students to Indigenous Peoples' food, nutrition, and health issues. Using the concept of food security as a framework, food availability, accessibility, adequacy, and acceptability will be discussed in the context of historical and current Indigenous food systems. Through lectures and class discussions, topics covered include: colonization and reconciliation; Indigenous worldviews; oral history and food; traditional foods; the social determinants of health; emerging health trends; food policy, community nutrition, and Indigenous food sovereignty.</p>
    





</div>
