                        <a id="accordion-1593530441785-hst-680---natives---newcomers-from-1763" role="tab" data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#" href="#accordion-content-1593530441785-hst-680---natives---newcomers-from-1763" aria-controls="accordion-content-1593530441785-hst-680---natives---newcomers-from-1763" aria-expanded="false">
                            HST 680 – Natives &amp; Newcomers from 1763
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    
                </div>
                <!-- Accordion Body -->
                <div tabindex="0" id="accordion-content-1593530441785-hst-680---natives---newcomers-from-1763" class="panel-collapse collapse" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="accordion-1593530441785-hst-680---natives---newcomers-from-1763">
                    <div class="panel-body ">
                        <div class="1593530441785 stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="24116a62-ef59-44a6-b456-251ff3cf82c3" >

    <p>How did the First Nations of the Great Lakes defend their interests when settlers flooded the region after 1763? What happened to them in the American Revolution and other frontier conflicts? What were the results for natives when Euroamericans forced them onto reservations or demanded they assimilate? What were the impacts of modernization after 1850? Explore these and other critical issues in native-newcomer relations in this course.</p>
    





</div>
