<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="2ee349f4-71cd-4abe-b3d2-10cda49885af" >

    <p>An introduction to Aboriginal worldviews in Canada with reference to Aboriginal worldviews globally. Students will be introduced to Aboriginal perspectives, values and spirituality. It includes an exploration of what constitutes "valid" knowledge, how knowledge shapes identity and how it influences the lives of Aboriginal peoples today. The role of worldviews as the basis of social justice and transformative change with the message that Aboriginal/ Indigenous knowledges can be of value to all people of the world.</p>
    





</div>
