<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="94dcba85-4278-40bb-847a-48a6772b7bdd" >

    <p>This course explores Aboriginal media art in the context of the major political and social discourses currently informing contemporary First Nations art. Through screenings, readings and guest artists we will examine critically engaged community-based art practices in the context of Aboriginal aesthetics. Two-spirit, gender, class and race issues will be seen through the lens of Aboriginal artists. The course will compare the function of art from an Aboriginal worldview with that of a Western one.</p>
    





</div>
