<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="3bdceb30-9cc1-41b5-ac3e-2bbab2cd914e" >

    <p>This course examines the social, political, legal, and historical context of Indigenous peoples in Canada and their political mobilization. Through an exploration of key challenges, flash points, and current issues, the course will foster a better understanding of Indigenous efforts around self-government, nation-building, recognition/implementation of Aboriginal and treaty rights, land claims, and the socio-economic gap that disadvantages Indigenous peoples in Canada.</p>
    





</div>
